This paper is about distributed consensus algorithms, which are typically studied in the Distributed Computing (cs.DC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also discusses safety and liveness properties, which are important in the context of security (cs.CR) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions TLA+ specifications, which are a formal language for specifying and verifying concurrent systems, and are typically studied in the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category.
